# Further Improvements?
[@v4g](/v4g) had a great improvement that gave better time.
Instead of sorting we can simply use **multiset** with reverse order and take the last element every time.
In `C++`: Since we are pointing to `multiset.end()` then it will be in `O(1)` and erasing the element given its iterator it also will be `O(1)`.

- **Time complexity:** $$O(Elog(N))$$
Since we loop over list of tickets with size `E` and each node can have at most `N` airports that you can travel to them. 
- **Space complexity:** $$O(N+E)$$
It still the same.

Here is the code for C++ and the solution can be generalized to other languages as well.

