Greedy strategy  + post order traversal
1. build a map to store each departure location and its destinations array.
2. sort the destinations array.
3. now we assume that the departure airport 'JFK' is the root node for this tree, and its destinations are the children. Since the destinations are sorted, the children are arranged alfabetically from left to right. For each destination, if it is also a departure airport, then its children are the related destinations. Hopefully by now you get an idea of the structure of the tree.
4. run a post order traversal of the tree , as a result, 'JFK' now is the last airport visited, hence the Greedy part. 
5. finally we reverse the result as the return value.


```
var findItinerary = function(tickets) {
    var map = {};
    var res = [];
    for(var i=0; i<tickets.length; i++) {
        var dep = tickets[i][0];
        var des = tickets[i][1];
        if(map[dep]) {
            map[dep].push(des);
        } else {
            map[dep] = [des];
        }
    }
    for(let loc in map) {
        map[loc].sort();
    }  
    var dfs = function(node) {
        var des = map[node];
        while(des && des.length>0) {
            dfs(des.shift());
        }
        res.push(node);
    }
    dfs('JFK');
    return res.reverse();
};
```

